      <title>Re: Cannot type on mobile platforms (iPhone / i...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezoe2/forum/general/cannot_type_on_mobile_platforms_iphone_ipad_android/re_cannot_type_on_mobile_platforms_iphone_i3</link>
      <description>Try to debug with this:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
Index: trunk/ezoe/ezxmltext/handlers/input/ezoexmlinput.php&#13;
===================================================================&#13;
--- trunk/ezoe/ezxmltext/handlers/input/ezoexmlinput.php	(revision 262)&#13;
+++ trunk/ezoe/ezxmltext/handlers/input/ezoexmlinput.php	(working copy)&#13;
@@ -194,6 +194,7 @@&#13;
                 if ( $browserInfo[1] &gt;= 522.0 )&#13;
                     self::$browserType = 'WebKit';&#13;
             }&#13;
+            var_dump( self::$browserType );&#13;
             if ( self::$browserType === false )&#13;
                 eZDebug::writeNotice( 'Browser not supported: ' . $userAgent, __METHOD__ );&#13;
         }&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
It should return false, meaning browser is not supported and eZ Publish should fallback to normal ezxmltext text area.&#13;
If it does not work as described above, please mention your ezoe + eZ Publish version.</description>
